He also accused Kuwait of stealing $2. The crisis began July 17 when Saddam accused Kuwait of trying to wreck the debt-ridden Iraqi economy with oil overproduction and began massing troops on Kuwait's border. The invaders were led by the elite Republican Guard that did the brunt of the fighting in the 1980-88 war with Iran. Iraq said in a statement that it had responded to the request from interim government of free Kuwait and decided to cooperate with it. Iraq also sealed its own borders and airspace. 